curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/8395' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM42500", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM42500 device is a brushed DC motor driver.  This device integrates four N-MOSFETs, which can  supply up to 3.6A peak current at 40V voltage.  The SGM42500 supports IN1/IN2 PWM interface. The  PWM signal can be implemented on the input interface  to adjust motor speed. Customer can adjust PWM  current limit or torque in real-time by VREF pin with a  controller’s DAC output or PWM signal after RC filter.  A number of protection features are provided in the  device including over-current, short-circuit, under-voltage  lockout and thermal shutdown. When the fault condition  is removed, the device automatically resumes normal  operation.  The SGM42500 is available in a Green SOIC-8  (Exposed Pad) package.   "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/8396' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM42500", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES  ● H-Bridge Motor Driver  ● Operating Voltage Range: 7V to 40V  ● Low On-Resistance: 0.41Ω (HS + LS) at +25℃  ● 3.6A Peak Output Current  ● Interface: IN1/IN2  ● Adjustable PWM Current Limit in Real-Time  ● Low Power Standby Mode  ● Integrated Protection Features    Over-Current Protection (OCP)    Under-Voltage Lockout (UVLO)    Thermal Shutdown (TSD)    Auto-Retry  ● Available in a Green SOIC-8 (Exposed Pad) Package      "}'
